A man has been airlifted to a London hospital after a crash involving a car and a motorbike.It happened in Broadstairs, Kent, at the junction of Sacketts Hill and St Peter's Road, about 15:35 BST on Sunday.The vehicles involved were a red, white, and black Yamaha Fazer motorbike and a white Ford Fiesta.Police said the injured man, who is in his 20s, is in a serious condition, and are appealing for witnesses or anyone with dashcam footage to get in contact.
